#: ../../hardware/controllers/reloop_beatpad.md:1
msgid "Reloop Beatpad"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/reloop_beatpad.md:4
msgid ""
"The **Reloop Beatpad** is a conventional 2 channel controller that is "
"primarily designed to work with algoriddim‘s djay on the iOS platform and "
"more recently on the Android platform, but can also be used with Mixxx by "
"sending MIDI signals to a computer with a USB cable."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/reloop_beatpad.md:9
msgid "[Manufacturer’s product page](http://www.reloop.com/reloop-beatpad)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/reloop_beatpad.md:10
msgid ""
"[Forum thread](https://mixxx.discourse.group/t/reloop-beatpad-ready-"
"for-1-12/15408)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/reloop_beatpad.md:14
msgid "Mixer Section"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/reloop_beatpad.md:17
msgid "Crossfader"
msgstr "Crossfader"

#: ../../hardware/controllers/reloop_beatpad.md:20
msgid "Blends audio between left and right mixer channels."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/reloop_beatpad.md:22
msgid "Volume Faders"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/reloop_beatpad.md:25
msgid ""
"Adjust the Volume of each channel. If {ref}`Fader Start <reloop-beatpad-"
"trackselect>` is enabled the deck will stop at the previously used Cue if "
"the Volume Fader reaches the minimum position and will start playing if the "
"Volume fader moves from the minimum position."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/reloop_beatpad.md:32
msgid "1 and 2 (Track select buttons)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/reloop_beatpad.md:35
msgid ""
"**Load a track:** Press these buttons to load the selected track from the "
"Browser to left or right deck. The LED of the button will be on if the deck "
"is loaded."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/reloop_beatpad.md:38
msgid ""
"**Eject:** Hold the same button for more than half of a second to unload the"
" same deck."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/reloop_beatpad.md:40
msgid ""
"**Fader Start:** Hold {ref}`SHIFT <reloop-beatpad-shift>` down and then "
"press one of these buttons to enable the **Fader Start** on a deck. The LED "
"of the button will blink if Fader Start is enabled. If Fader Start is "
"enabled the deck will stop at the previously used Cue if the Volume Fader "
"reaches the minimum position and will start playing if the Volume fader "
"moves from the minimum position."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/reloop_beatpad.md:46
msgid "PFL (symbolized by a headphone)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/reloop_beatpad.md:49
msgid ""
"\\**PFL: \\**Press these buttons to send each channel to the Headphones "
"Output channel for pre-listening."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/reloop_beatpad.md:51
msgid ""
"\\**Slip mode: \\**Hold {ref}`SHIFT <reloop-beatpad-shift>` down and then "
"press these buttons to activate/deactivate Slip Mode. When active, the "
"playback continues muted in the background during a loop, scratch etc. Once "
"disabled, the audible playback will resume where the track would have been."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/reloop_beatpad.md:55
msgid ""
"**Quantize mode:** Hold {ref}`SHIFT <reloop-beatpad-shift>` down and then "
"press these buttons to activate/deactivate the Quantize mode. When active, "
"it aligns Hot-cues and Loops to the next beat from the current position."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/reloop_beatpad.md:59
msgid "Equalizer"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/reloop_beatpad.md:62
msgid "**LOW:** Adjust the Low (Bass) frequencies for each mixer channel."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/reloop_beatpad.md:63
msgid "**MID:** Adjust the Mid frequencies for each mixer channel."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/reloop_beatpad.md:64
msgid "**HIGH:** Adjust the High (Treble) frequencies for each mixer channel."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/reloop_beatpad.md:65
msgid "**GAIN:** Adjust the Gain of each mixer channel."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/reloop_beatpad.md:66
msgid "**MASTER:** Adjust the level of the Master Output."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/reloop_beatpad.md:67
msgid ""
"**Cue Mix (Hadphones mixing):** Adjust how the Channels and the Master "
"Output blend at the Headphones Channel."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/reloop_beatpad.md:69
msgid ""
"**Phones (Hadphones level):** Adjust the Volume Output of the Headphones "
"Channel."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/reloop_beatpad.md:71
msgid "**AUX:** Adjust the Volume of the AUX Input."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/reloop_beatpad.md:73
msgid ""
"The MASTER, Phones, and AUX knobs adjust the levels of the Beatpad’s sound "
"card; they do not control the software gains in Mixxx so the changes are not"
" visible on screen."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/reloop_beatpad.md:79
msgid "REC"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/reloop_beatpad.md:82
msgid ""
"**Record:** Use this button to start/stop recording your mixing session."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/reloop_beatpad.md:83
msgid ""
"**End track warning:** Hold {ref}`SHIFT <reloop-beatpad-shift>` down and "
"then press this button in order to toggle **on** or **off** the red flashing"
" of the {ref}`jog wheels <reloop-beatpad-jogwheel>` when the playback "
"reaches the end of the track."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/reloop_beatpad.md:87
msgid "Browse Knob"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/reloop_beatpad.md:90
msgid "Scroll through your library."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/reloop_beatpad.md:92
msgid "**Turn** to select a track in the song list."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/reloop_beatpad.md:93
msgid "**Push** to load the selected track into first stop deck."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/reloop_beatpad.md:94
msgid ""
"{ref}`SHIFT <reloop-beatpad-shift>`**+Turn** to select a folder or subfolder"
" in the left item list sidebar."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/reloop_beatpad.md:96
msgid ""
"{ref}`SHIFT <reloop-beatpad-shift>`**+Push** to open/close folders and "
"subfolders in the left item list sidebar."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/reloop_beatpad.md:99
msgid "Deck Controls Section"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/reloop_beatpad.md:104
msgid "SHIFT"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/reloop_beatpad.md:107
msgid ""
"Press and hold one of those buttons to access secondary functions of other "
"controls on the Beatpad. The secondary functions can be accessed while the "
"**SHIFT** button is held down. If the **SHIFT LOCK** switch on the back side"
" of the Reloop Beatpad is on, the secondary functions can be accessed after "
"the button **SHIFT** button is released and until the **SHIFT** is pressed "
"again."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/reloop_beatpad.md:115
msgid "PLAY/PAUSE"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/reloop_beatpad.md:118
msgid ""
"**Play/pause:** Press to play/pause the track. If there was no track loaded "
"into the deck and a track is selected in the library, it is loaded and "
"starts playing."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/reloop_beatpad.md:121
msgid ""
"**Censor:** Hold {ref}`SHIFT <reloop-beatpad-shift>` down and then press "
"this button to play the track in reverse. When released the track will "
"continue to play from the position it would have been if the button was "
"never pressed. In other words, it enables reverse and slip mode while held."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/reloop_beatpad.md:128
msgid "JUMP"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/reloop_beatpad.md:131
msgid ""
"**While playing, or stopped:** If the Cue point is set, seeks the player to "
"it and starts playback."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/reloop_beatpad.md:133
msgid ""
"**Brake:** Hold {ref}`SHIFT <reloop-beatpad-shift>` down and then press this"
" button to stop the track with a gradual brake. If the **JUMP** button is "
"released before the track has completely stopped, the track is then played "
"back to its regular speed."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/reloop_beatpad.md:137
msgid ""
"**Spinback:** see the {ref}`Instant FX <reloop-beatpad-instantfx>` usage."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/reloop_beatpad.md:139
msgid "SET"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/reloop_beatpad.md:142
msgid "**While playing:** Seeks the track to the cue-point and stops."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/reloop_beatpad.md:143
msgid ""
"**While stopped:** Sets the cue point (Pioneer/Mixxx mode) OR preview from "
"it (Denon mode). If the Cue point is already set at the current position of "
"the track, hold this button to play the track and release it to return to "
"the Cue point and pause it. To continue playback without returning to the "
"Cue Point, press and hold the **SET** Button, then press and hold the "
"{ref}`Play/Pause <reloop-beatpad-playpause>` Button and then release both "
"buttons."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/reloop_beatpad.md:150
msgid ""
"**Key lock:** Hold {ref}`SHIFT <reloop-beatpad-shift>` down and then press "
"this button to enable/disable the Key-lock."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/reloop_beatpad.md:154
msgid ""
"Change the default cue mode in Preferences -> Interface. The Pioneer mode is"
" the more consistent with the Reloop Beatpad."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/reloop_beatpad.md:157
msgid "SYNC"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/reloop_beatpad.md:160
msgid ""
"**Press once** to synchronize the tempo (BPM) and phase to that of the other"
" track."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/reloop_beatpad.md:162
msgid ""
"**Press twice quickly** to play the track immediately, synchronized to the "
"tempo (BPM) and to the phase of the other track, if the track was paused."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/reloop_beatpad.md:164
msgid ""
"**Sync Lock:** Hold for at least half of a second to enable **sync lock** "
"for this deck. Decks with sync locked will all play at the same tempo, and "
"decks that also have **quantize** enabled (which is enabled by default by "
"the mapping) will always have their beats lined up. **Note :** the "
"**quantize** mode is not mapped on the controller but can be "
"enabled/disabled from Mixxx."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/reloop_beatpad.md:173
msgid "Jogwheel"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/reloop_beatpad.md:176
msgid ""
"Touch sensitive platters for scratching (Scratch mode/iCut mode), bending   "
"(Scratch mode/CD mode) or Seek mode.<br> The jogwheel offers multi-color "
"leds, which will show the playing marker   (Scratch mode), the song progress"
" bar (in Seek mode), and other colored   combinations depending on the "
"applied effect, loop, loop roll or Filter. If no   track is loaded, the "
"jogwheel displays a red cross. At the end of a track, the   jogwheel is "
"flashing red faster and faster until it reaches the end of the   track (full"
" steady red).<br> You can toggle on/off this behavior with {ref}`SHIFT "
"<reloop-beatpad-shift>` + {ref}`REC <reloop-beatpad-rec>`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/reloop_beatpad.md:188
msgid "Scratch mode"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/reloop_beatpad.md:191
msgid ""
"Toggle with the **JOG SCRATCH** button.<br> Use the jogwheel to scratch and "
"the outer ring to bend (like in {ref}`CD mode <reloop-beatpad-cdmode>`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/reloop_beatpad.md:194
msgid ""
"**iCut mode:** Hold {ref}`SHIFT <reloop-beatpad-shift>` down and scratch to "
"scratch in “automagic” scratch mode. When the jog wheel is turned back, the "
"crossfader is closed. When the jog wheel is turned forward, the crossfader "
"opens. (Note that the Algoriddim djay mapping actually closes/opens the "
"crossfader quickly without taking into account the direction of the wheel, "
"contrary to what the Beatpad’s Quick Start guide says.)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/reloop_beatpad.md:203
msgid "Seek mode"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/reloop_beatpad.md:206
msgid ""
"Toggle with the **JOG SEEK** button.<br> Use the jogwheel to navigate "
"through the track."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/reloop_beatpad.md:212
msgid "CD mode"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/reloop_beatpad.md:215
msgid ""
"Deactivate both the {ref}`Scratch mode <reloop-beatpad-scratchmode>` and the"
" {ref}`Seek mode <reloop-beatpad-seekmode>` to enable this mode.<br> Use the"
" jogwheel to temporarily bend the pitch of the track (which only   affects "
"the tempo with keylock on)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/reloop_beatpad.md:219
msgid "PITCH BEND"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/reloop_beatpad.md:222
msgid ""
"**Pitch bend:** Use these buttons temporary slow-down/speed up the tempo of "
"the track. Once the buttons are released the track will continue to play at "
"the tempo designated by the pitch fader."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/reloop_beatpad.md:226
msgid ""
"**Beat Jump:** Hold {ref}`SHIFT <reloop-beatpad-shift>` down and then use "
"these buttons to jump 1 beat backwards or forward."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/reloop_beatpad.md:229
msgid "PITCH"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/reloop_beatpad.md:232
msgid ""
"Controls the track’s pitch. With keylock on, this only changes the tempo. "
"The red LED indicates that the pitch fader of the unit is on zero (center) "
"position."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/reloop_beatpad.md:237
msgid "Loops Section"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/reloop_beatpad.md:240
msgid ""
"**Loop size:** Turn the encoder to select the number of beats for a loop. "
"Turn it counterclockwise to half the size of the loop and clockwise to "
"double it."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/reloop_beatpad.md:243
msgid ""
"**Loop move:** Hold {ref}`SHIFT <reloop-beatpad-shift>` down and then use "
"the encoder to move the triggered loop forward or backwards by 1 beat."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/reloop_beatpad.md:245
msgid ""
"**Activate/deactivate:** (Acts exactly like the {ref}`LOOP <reloop-beatpad-"
"loops>` Button)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/reloop_beatpad.md:246
msgid ""
"**Regular loop mode:** Push (and release) the encoder to trigger a loop of "
"the selected size"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/reloop_beatpad.md:248
msgid ""
"**Roll loop mode:** Press (and hold down) to trigger a momentary rolling "
"loop of the selected size. While the encoder is held down, the track will "
"keep moving forward as if it was not looping, so when the encoder is "
"released, it will jump forward to where the track would have been if the "
"rolling loop was never enabled. In other words, this is a regular loop in "
"slip mode."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/reloop_beatpad.md:253
msgid ""
"**Toggle loop mode:** Hold {ref}`SHIFT <reloop-beatpad-shift>` down and then"
" push the encoder to toggle between Regular and Roll Loop mode."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/reloop_beatpad.md:257
msgid ""
"Rolling loops can be set using the {ref}`Bounce Loop (Roll) mode <reloop-"
"beatpad-rollmode>`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/reloop_beatpad.md:261
msgid "Effects Section"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/reloop_beatpad.md:264
msgid "FX ON"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/reloop_beatpad.md:267
msgid ""
"Push (and release) this button to trigger the selected effect chain for the "
"corresponding deck (toggle function)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/reloop_beatpad.md:270
msgid "FX SELECT"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/reloop_beatpad.md:273
msgid ""
"**Select:** Use this encoder to select an effect for the current selected "
"rack."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/reloop_beatpad.md:275
msgid ""
"**Temporary effect:** Push and hold the encoder to temporarily apply the "
"effect of the current selected rack for the corresponding deck (while "
"pressed)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/reloop_beatpad.md:278
msgid ""
"**Quick Effect:** Hold {ref}`SHIFT <reloop-beatpad-shift>` down and then "
"push the encoder Activate or Kill the **Quick Effect**. You can change the "
"Quick effect assigned in Mixxx, via Options -> Settings-> Equalizers -> "
"Quick Effect."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/reloop_beatpad.md:282
msgid "FX PARAM"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/reloop_beatpad.md:285
msgid ""
"**SUPER:** Use this knob to control the **SUPER** parameter of the effect "
"for the current selected rack."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/reloop_beatpad.md:287
msgid ""
"**MIX:** Hold {ref}`SHIFT <reloop-beatpad-shift>` down and then use this "
"knob to control the **MIX** parameter of the effect for the current selected"
" rack."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/reloop_beatpad.md:290
msgid "FILTER"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/reloop_beatpad.md:293
msgid ""
"**Quick Effect:** Use this knob to apply the Quick effect (by default, this "
"is Filter, but you can change it) to the deck. In middle position no effect "
"is applied for filter."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/reloop_beatpad.md:296
msgid ""
"**Key:** Hold SHIFT down and use this knob to adjust the key (pitch) of the "
"track without changing the tempo. In middle position the track will have its"
" original key."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/reloop_beatpad.md:300
msgid "Pads Section"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/reloop_beatpad.md:303
msgid ""
"The 4 Performance Pads offer 4 different modes, depending on the 4 PAD MODE "
"buttons just above."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/reloop_beatpad.md:306
msgid "HotCues mode"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/reloop_beatpad.md:309
msgid "CUE"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/reloop_beatpad.md:312
msgid "Press the **CUE** mode button to set the PADs to HOT CUE mode."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/reloop_beatpad.md:314
#: ../../hardware/controllers/reloop_beatpad.md:333
#: ../../hardware/controllers/reloop_beatpad.md:368
msgid "Pads"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/reloop_beatpad.md:317
msgid ""
"**Press** each one of the 4 pads to assign a Hot Cue Point (1 to 4) or "
"returns the track to that Hot Cue Point. When a Hot Cue Button is unlit, you"
" can assign a Hot Cue Point by pressing it at the desired point in your "
"track. Once it is assigned, the Hot Cue Button will light up blue."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/reloop_beatpad.md:321
msgid ""
"** {ref}`SHIFT <reloop-beatpad-shift>` + Press** to delete its assigned Hot "
"Cue Point."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/reloop_beatpad.md:325
msgid "Bounce Loop (Roll) mode"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/reloop_beatpad.md:328
msgid "BOUNCE LOOP"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/reloop_beatpad.md:331
msgid ""
"Press the **BOUNCE LOOP** mode button to set the PADs to Loop Roll mode."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/reloop_beatpad.md:336
msgid ""
"Press (and keep down) any of the 4 pads to trigger a momentary {ref}`Loop "
"Roll <interface-looping>` of a different size (in beats) as per the table."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/reloop_beatpad.md:340
msgid ""
"===================+++++===================== === === === === Pads"
"                                            1   2   3   4 Press"
"                                         1/8 1/4 1/2   1 {ref}`SHIFT "
"<reloop-beatpad-shift>` + Press     2   4   8  16 "
"===========++================================ === === === ==="
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/reloop_beatpad.md:346
msgid ""
"Once the PAD is released the track will continue to play from the position "
"it would have been if the Loop Roll was never triggered. The size of the "
"applied Loop Roll can be adjusted with the {ref}`LOOP SIZE <reloop-beatpad-"
"loops>` encoder as well. Pads change the “selected loop size” introduced in "
"{ref}`LOOP SIZE <reloop-beatpad-loops>` and {ref}`LOOP <reloop-beatpad-"
"loops>` sections."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/reloop_beatpad.md:352
msgid "Instant FX mode"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/reloop_beatpad.md:357
msgid "Instant FX"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/reloop_beatpad.md:360
msgid "**Press** this button to set the PADs to Effects mode."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/reloop_beatpad.md:361
msgid ""
"**Spinback:** Hold {ref}`SHIFT <reloop-beatpad-shift>` down and then press "
"this button down in order to stop the track with a backward brake effect. If"
" the Instant FX button is released before the track has completely stopped, "
"the track is then played back to its regular speed, in the forward "
"direction."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/reloop_beatpad.md:366
msgid "**Brake :** see {ref}`JUMP <reloop-beatpad-jump>` button usage"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/reloop_beatpad.md:371
msgid ""
"**Instant FX:** Press (and keep down) any of the 4 pads to apply momentarily"
" the effect of the corresponding effect rack. The parameters of these "
"effects can be adjusted from the {ref}`FX PARAM <reloop-beatpad-effects>` "
"knob."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/reloop_beatpad.md:374
msgid ""
"**Current effect rack selection:** Hold {ref}`SHIFT <reloop-beatpad-shift>` "
"down and then press any of the 4 pads to select the current effect rack for "
"this deck that will be used for effect selection or for the corresponding "
"effect to be triggered later on (see {ref}`Effects Section <reloop-beatpad-"
"effects>`). this can also be done with a visual feedback in {ref}`Sampler "
"mode <reloop-beatpad-samplermode>`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/reloop_beatpad.md:382
msgid "Sampler mode"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/reloop_beatpad.md:385
msgid ""
"**Note:** On account of the Reloop Beatpad limitations (bug ?), lights will "
"not show on in Sampler mode when the controller is in {ref}`SHIFT <reloop-"
"beatpad-shift>` mode."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/reloop_beatpad.md:388
msgid ""
"Press the SAMPLER mode button to set the PADs to cycle between 4 sub modes:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/reloop_beatpad.md:390
msgid ""
"**Sampler mode** (orange LEDs): each pad triggers a sample from the selected"
" Sampler bank. The PADs wgich are lit indicate which samples are loaded and "
"ready to use. While a sample is playing, the corresponding PAD changes its "
"color to pink."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/reloop_beatpad.md:391
msgid ""
"**Sampler bank selection mode** (pink LED): each pad selects 1 of the 4 "
"sampler banks. The PAD that is lit indicates which bank is active."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/reloop_beatpad.md:392
msgid ""
"**Loop mode** status and selection (magenta LEDs): press any pad to toggle "
"between {ref}`regular loop mode <reloop-beatpad-loops>` and {ref}`roll loop "
"mode <reloop-beatpad-loops>`. **Regular loop mode** is symbolized by the "
"left PAD lit, representing the loop), and all the others switched off. "
"**Roll loop mode** is symbolized by both the left (representing the loop) "
"and the right PADs lit (symbolizing the position after the loop where the "
"track will continue to play when the loop will be triggered off)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/reloop_beatpad.md:393
msgid ""
"**Effect rack selection** mode (purple LED): each pads selects 1 of the 4 "
"effect racks. The PAD which is lit indicates which effect rack is active "
"(see {ref}`Effect Section <reloop-beatpad-effects>`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/reloop_beatpad.md:395
msgid "Troubleshooting"
msgstr "Depanarea"

#: ../../hardware/controllers/reloop_beatpad.md:398
msgid "Grounding problem"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/reloop_beatpad.md:401
msgid ""
"If your controller randomly freezes or your iPad or Android tablet acts "
"weirdly (screen flashing, bad sound), make a home made, grounded power "
"cable."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/reloop_beatpad.md:404
msgid "Controller not detected by Windows"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/reloop_beatpad.md:407
msgid ""
"If you see a yellow exclamation point (!) in the Windows Device Manager "
"indicating that the drivers did not start, unplug the power cable from your "
"laptop then unplug/replug the USB cable from your controller. If that does "
"not work, restart your laptop without the power cable plugged in."
msgstr ""
